Identifiers
    * This are the name event given to the
        - Variables
        - Functions
        - Classes
    which is used to identify the functionality often.

Rules of Identifiers:
    1) It should not be a keywords.
    2) It should not start with numbers.
    3) It should not contain any special characters except '_' (underscore).
    4) It can be
        - Alphabets(uppercase/lowercase)
        - Alphanumeric
        - '_'(underscore)

Examples of Identifiers:
    - my_name
    - bond007
    - her_age
    - phone_numbers
    - list_of__items
    - school_names
    - movie1

Note:
    Industrial Standard Rule
        - According to this convention, the length of the variable name should not exceed 32 characters.